03/12/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- European Commission (EC) Director for the Western Balkans Pierre Mirel confirmed in Pristina on Tuesday (December 2nd) that Kosovo has entered the feasibility study phase, a first step towards signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with the EU. "In a sense, we have started studying feasibility today by assessing some of the concrete issues mentioned in the [EC] progress report," said Mirel during the 15th meeting of the SAA Tracking Mechanisms for Kosovo. He added that this confirms the EC's engagement in Kosovo. (Koha Ditore, Zeri, Kosova Sot - 03/12/08; RTK, Telegrafi - 02/12/08)
